DirectoryAttributeCollection Class

In this Article

The DirectoryAttributeCollection class contains a collection of DirectoryAttribute objects.

    Exception Condition

    -or-

    The number of elements in the source DirectoryAttributeCollection is greater than the available space from index to the end of the destination array.
    InvalidCastException The type of the source DirectoryAttributeCollection cannot be cast automatically to the type of the destination array.

    The Insert method inserts the specified DirectoryAttribute object into the DirectoryAttributeCollection at the specified index.

    public void Insert (int index, System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DirectoryAttribute value);

    Parameters

    • index
      Int32

      The zero-based index point, in the collection, at which to insert the DirectoryAttribute object.

      value is a null reference (Nothing in Visual Basic) or value specifies a modification operation other than Add.

    • ArgumentOutOfRangeException

    protected override void OnValidate (object value);

      The object to evaluate.

    Exceptions

    • ArgumentException

      This exception can occur under one of the following conditions:

      • value is a null reference (Nothing in Visual Basic).

      • value is not a DirectoryAttribute object.
